---
source: tests/cli_golden.rs
expression: help
---
Run the agent (default when no subcommand is given)

Usage: aura run [OPTIONS]

Options:
      --mode <MODE>
          Phase 9: top-level `AgentMode` override. Highest rung of the documented resolution priority chain (CLI > TUI slash > SDK field > daemon default > `AgentMode::Agent` fallback). The flag is resolved at session start by the fleet daemon's `resolve_session_mode` helper

          Possible values:
          - agent: Full unrestricted operation subject to user permissions
          - plan:  Read + markdown writes + read-only subprocesses
          - ask:   Read-only
          - debug: Read + sandboxed probes only

      --ui <UI>
          UI mode (terminal or none)

          Possible values:
          - terminal: Full terminal UI (default)
          - none:     No UI, run as swarm server
          
          [default: terminal]

      --theme <THEME>
          Theme (cyber, matrix, synthwave, minimal)
          
          [default: cyber]

  -d, --dir <DIR>
          Working directory

      --provider <PROVIDER>
          Model provider (anthropic or mock)
          
          [default: anthropic]

  -v, --verbose
          Enable verbose output

      --allow-unrestricted-full-access
          Permit FullAccess sessions to bypass command allowlists

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')
